# 4π cumulative-sum analysis — web app

Frontend/backend split. The backend computes; the frontend only renders.

## Architecture

```
frontend/                 vanilla JS/HTML/CSS — no build step
  index.html              DOM skeleton (populated by app.js)
  style.css               all styles + processing overlay
  app.js                  fetch → render tables/chart, upload, overlay

backend/
  app.py                  Flask: HTTP routes only, no math
  requirements.txt
  data/fourpi.bin         default dataset (loaded on startup)
  core/                   the computation engine (swappable)
    analysis.py           PURE functions: cumsum, k·2ⁿ, metrics, stats
    engine.py             backend selector — the seam for a future C++ core
    __init__.py
```

### The data contract

Frontend and backend communicate over one JSON shape (the dict returned by
`core.analysis.analyze`). The frontend never computes; it draws whatever the
backend sends.

```
Frontend (JS)  <->  Flask (app.py)  <->  engine.py  ->  [ Python core ]
                                                      \->  [ C++ binary ]  (future)
```

### Swapping in C++ later

`engine.py` is the only file that knows *how* the analysis runs. To move the
heavy number-crunching to C++, set `BACKEND = "cpp"` and implement `_run_cpp`
(call a compiled binary via subprocess or a pybind11 module). The binary must
emit the same JSON dict. Flask and the frontend stay untouched.

## Run

```bash
cd backend
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
# open http://127.0.0.1:5000
```

On startup the app loads `backend/data/fourpi.bin`. Use the **Raw data → New
data** toolbar menu to upload a different `.bin`.

## Accepted input

A `.bin` file that is a digit stream, auto-detected as either:
- one byte per digit, values `0..9` (like `fourpi.bin`), or
- ASCII digit characters `'0'..'9'` (bytes 48..57).

Anything else is rejected with a clear error (HTTP 422).

## API

| Method | Path                    | Purpose                                  |
|--------|-------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| GET    | `/`                     | serve `index.html`                       |
| GET    | `/<file>`               | serve frontend assets                    |
| GET    | `/api/analyze/default`  | analyze bundled `fourpi.bin`             |
| POST   | `/api/analyze`          | multipart upload, returns analysis JSON  |